    <h1>crosswalk.titles.media</h1>
    <p>A static JSON API mapping film identities across IMDB, TMDB, Wikidata, and Letterboxd.</p>
    <p>Full documentation: <a href="https://github.com/titles-media/crosswalk">titles-media/crosswalk</a> on GitHub.</p>

    <h2>Endpoints</h2>

    <p>Look up a film by internal ID:</p>
    <pre><code>{BASE}/movies/&#123;id&#125;.json</code></pre>

    <p>Look up a film by external ID:</p>
    <pre><code>{BASE}/movies/by_id/&#123;source&#125;/&#123;source_id&#125;.json</code></pre>
    <p>Supported sources: <code>imdb</code>, <code>tmdb</code>, <code>wikidata</code>, <code>letterboxd</code></p>

    <h2>Example</h2>
    <pre><code><a href="/movies/by_id/imdb/tt12042730.json">{BASE}/movies/by_id/imdb/tt12042730.json</a></code></pre>
    <pre><code><a href="/movies/p148c7y3.json">{BASE}/movies/p148c7y3.json</a></code></pre>
    <pre>{JSON.stringify({
      id: "p148c7y3",
      title: "Project Hail Mary",
      year: 2026,
      imdb_id: "tt12042730",
      letterboxd_id: "project-hail-mary",
      tmdb_id: "687163",
      wikidata_id: "Q107105860"
    }, null, 2)}</pre>

    <h2>Response shape</h2>
    <p>All endpoints return a <code>full</code> record. Fields:</p>
    <pre><code>
id            internal Blake2b ID (always present)
title         film title (always present)
year          release year (always present)
imdb_id       may be absent
tmdb_id       may be absent
wikidata_id   may be absent
letterboxd_id may be absent
</code></pre>
  </body>
